metadata.name: ELEDA (The Creator)
metadata.description:
‘ELEDA’ is a Yoruba word that means ‘The Creator’. It is a term often used to refer to God, acknowledging him as the supreme and ultimate creator of all things. 

It is also believed that men inherited this ability of God - the ability to create. 

‘Then God said, “Let us make mankind in our image, in our likeness”.
